<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="8">
            <title>WHEEL DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Lubricate internal parts with gear lube during reassembly. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in
                        the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press bearing cones on support cases (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401622">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401622" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401622" filename="../figg14/G1401622.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 22. Bearing Cone Installation</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To prevent bearing cone damage, use suitable sleeve that only contacts the inner race of
                            the cone.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position high speed clutch plate with chamfered end of the clutch teeth toward idler
                    pinions. Press clutch plate on case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401623">Figure 23</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401624">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401623" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401623" filename="../figg14/G1401623.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 23. Pressing Clutch Plate On Case</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1401624" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401624" filename="../figg14/G1401624.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Plate Installation Specifications</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>It is important that the dowel pins are recessed 1/8 inch below the surface of the clutch
                            plate (
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401624">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place thrust washer and side gear in differential case/clutch plate subassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401625">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401625" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401625" filename="../figg14/G1401625.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Differential Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble side pinions and thrust washers on spider. Place this assembly in differential
                    case/clutch plate subassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401625">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place side gear and thrust washer in position on side pinions (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401625">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align punch marks and place plain case on differential case/clutch plate subassembly.
                    Install bolts and tighten. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s14016_HL1401602.xml" xrefid="hl1401602">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Turn side gear hub to check for free differential rotation. Rotation may require up to 50
                            ft-lbs. (68 N&#8226;m) torque.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install idler pins and pinions (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401626">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401626" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401626" filename="../figg14/G1401626.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Idler Pin and Pinion Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place thrust washer in large support case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401627">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401627" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401627" filename="../figg14/G1401627.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Thrust Washer Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">During installation of ring gear, temporarily use two bolts in mounting holes to assure
                    bolt hole alignment. Place ring gear on large support case, then remove the two bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401628">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401628" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401628" filename="../figg14/G1401628.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Ring Gear Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place support case and ring gear assembly upright on a bench. Carefully lower
                    differential assembly into case. Engage idler pinions with ring gear teeth to complete the
                    installation (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401629">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401629" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401629" filename="../figg14/G1401629.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Support Case Installation</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>During differential installation, be sure the thrust washer stays in its proper mounting
                            position.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install thrust washer and small support case over differential assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401629">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully install ring gear bolts and nuts, making certain flat on bolt head is seated
                    against the outside diameter of the large support case. Install and tighten nuts. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s14016_HL1401602.xml" xrefid="hl1401602">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Temporarily install sliding clutch (or sun gear) and check planetary for free rotation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
